<h2 class="tips">Tips</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>
A 100-peso note is about as useless for ordinary purchases in Buenos Aires as a 1,000-dollar bill is in the United States.  Store clerks, restaurant servers, and taxicab drivers are notably reluctant to change these large bills, and quite often have the same attitude about changing 50-peso notes. 
</p>

<p>
When you fetch money at the ATM, <strong>always</strong> request an odd amount in pesos&ndash;$190, for instance.  Buenos Aires ATMs dispense money in a range of denominations, and you will receive much more useful 5- and 10-peso notes.
</p>

